{
  "stem": "2578.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 19-- in the-- in the beginning of August of 1944, the German who was-- the German civilian who was in charge of the Lodz came into the ghetto, and he made speeches that the Russian army is coming closer to the-- to Lodz.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because we were such good workers for the German authorities, and for the German war effort, he wants to save us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, in order for us to be saved, the Lodz ghetto has to be evacuated-- not liquidated, but evacuated-- deep into Germany where we, because we were so good, we will work for the German authorities.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We will continue working under better conditions, under safe conditions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we should voluntarily go by groups into the trains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we will go into Germany, into special places where we will continue to work at the same places, in the same trades, in the same services as we did before.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Naturally, we did not believe them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we wouldn't go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the German soldiers came in and, by force, they started to move us out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And every day-- First of all, we stopped-- we stopped working.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had to move out from our homes into the plants where we worked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we stayed there until our next came to be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Our-- our transport, where I was with my family, left the ghetto on the 24th of August.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1944.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I understand that, two days later, Rumkowski with his family was shipped out from the ghetto into Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When our transport came to Auschwitz, the train stopped, the doors opened up-- this is a special chapter, a separate chapter, just to describe it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The conditions in that train, in that cattle-car train-- that it's supposed to-- normally, the trip would-- should take about six, seven hours.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
